create a test dev for the following tasks:
1. create a github repo for the web app
2. create a github separate repo for the test
3. in the test ci pipeline, run the test on each pull request
3.1. pull the latest code from the web app repo
3.2. run the test
3.3. upload the test results to the test repo
4. in the web app ci pipeline, run the test on each pull request before merging to main
4.1. pull the branch code from the web app repo
4.2. run the tests with 'smoke' tag
4.3. upload the test results to the web app repo
4.4. if the test fails, do not merge to main
4.5. if the test passes, merge to main then run the all tests on the latest code
4.6. upload the test results to the web app repo

Additional:
1. I want to use containers for the app and the test
